AETHERMUD ROLEPLAY WIZARD HANDBOOK

WHO THIS IS FOR
Staff who handle starting skills, RP fairness, skill requests, tattoos,
and player-facing support for character capabilities.

POSITION AND ROLE
  position: rp_wiz
  wiz_role: rp (synced automatically from position)

TOOLS YOU MUST HOLD
Granted on promotion:
  RP Skill Tool (commands: tool or rptool)
  Tattoo Gun (command: inscribe)
  Skill slip (for processing mailbox requests)

Your workroom also has a request mailbox object.

COMMAND ACCESS
Roleplay wizards do NOT get creator or admin command paths.
You CAN use:
  tool / rptool (via RP skill tool only)
  inscribe (via tattoo gun only)
  Mailbox verbs in your workroom: read mailbox, take request, read slip,
    approve slip, deny slip
  Ambassador file tools and workroom (same as all wizards)

RP SKILL TOOL MENU
  1. Select a player (required first)
  2. View player skills
  3. Grant a skill (name and percentage)
  4. Remove a skill
  5. Grant a language (proficiency percentage)
  6. Remove a language (cannot remove native languages)
  7. View skill request queue

TATTOO GUN MENU (inscribe)
For Atlantean and Tattooed Man characters:
  1. Select a player
  2. View tattoos
  3. Grant a tattoo (pick tattoo, then body location)
  4. Remove a tattoo by location number

SKILL REQUEST WORKFLOW
Players submit: requestskill <text>
In your workroom:
  read mailbox       list pending requests
  take request       pull oldest request as a slip
  read slip          view details
  approve slip       grant skill and percentage
  deny slip          discard request
Offline grants are saved and applied on next login.

DIRECTORY ACCESS
  Your workroom: /realms/<yourname>/workroom
  Skill request saves: /secure/save/skill_requests/
You do not receive a QCS area tree unless promoted to another role.

YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES
  Review and approve skill requests fairly
  Grant starting and elective skills within Rifts rules
  Manage Atlantean/Tattooed Man tattoos
  Support Domain and Admin on RP disputes and player-kill fairness
  Document unusual grants in wiz chat or mail to Domain/Admin

NOT YOUR JOB
  Building rooms, NPCs, or gear (Coding wizard)
  Creating /domains/ directories (Domain wizard)
  Promoting staff or wiping players (Admin)
  Using build, update, or QCS commands

Domain wizards may also use RP tools for oversight when holding the tool.

SEE ALSO
  help domain *wizard staff
  help admin *wizard staff
  read book (in your workroom)
